How explore in {loaderName} works?
- You can skip rounds like in base game
- You can filter rounds by it's type in config
- On survival rounds your time limit settings will be ignored
- To stop playing explore rounds use pause menu or {loaderName} GUI

- Create a new folder with the desired language code in the Localization folder (refer to language-codes.csv in the assets if needed).
- Duplicate "locale.csv" from existing localization folder and place it into your new folder.
- Open "locale.csv" via any CSV editor and change anything you want.
- Once done, save your changes in UTF-8 encoding (should be set by default setting).
- To use your localization with game, specify the folder name for "Localization File Name" in the config or use the {loaderName} GUI.
- If you want to translate config descriptions and credits, copy specific files for them (credits.txt and config-descs.txt) from existing localization and put them in your localization folder after that translate them same way.
- Feel free to submit your translations on the {loaderName} Discord server. Most likely they will be included with the mod in next updates.
